title: Quentin Bryce
summary: Dame Quentin Alice Louise Bryce, AD, CVO (n√©e Strachan; born 23 December 1942) is an Australian academic who served as the 25th Governor-General of Australia from 2008 to 2014. She is the first woman to have held the position, and was previously the 24th Governor of Queensland from 2003 to 2008.[1]
